      • readInputStream

        public static ByteBuffer readInputStream(HttpURLConnection urlConn)
                                  throws IOException
        An efficient common URL HTTP input stream reader. Returns a ByteBuffer containing the raw content bytes of a connection Populates the ByteBuffer result from the error stream if the responseCode is >= 400 && < 600.
        Parameters:
        urlConn - an active HTTP URL Connection
        Returns:
        a ByteBuffer containing the raw content bytes of a connection
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs during the operation

      • sendPOST

        public static String sendPOST(String myURL,
                              String[][] parameters,
                              String[][] headers,
                              String fileFormName,
                              String fileName,
                              File file,
                              int connectTimeout,
                              int readTimeout)
                       throws IOException,
                              NoSuchAlgorithmException,
                              KeyManagementException
        Sends a HTTP POST message with parameters, headers, and file.
        Parameters:
        myURL - the base URL
        parameters - optional query parameters as Name/Value pairs
        headers - optional headers as Name/Value pairs
        fileFormName - optional form field name for the file, defaults to "file"
        fileName - optional name to give the posted file, defaults to file.getName()
        file - optional file to send
        connectTimeout - the connection timeout value in millseconds
        readTimeout - the read timeout value in millseconds
        Returns:
        the response of the POST
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs during the operation
        NoSuchAlgorithmException - if the "SSL" protocol is not available
        KeyManagementException - if unable to initialize the SSL context

      • encodeURIComponent

        public static String encodeURIComponent(String s)
        Creates a percent encoded string. The original string is extracted using the UTF-8 codeset. We may NOT use URLEncoder.encode(param[0], "UTF-8") because it converts (' ' to '+')
        Parameters:
        s - the string to URI encode
        Returns:
        a URI encoded component
        See Also:
        https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986
